# SSL Inc. - MVP Product Requirements Document

## Executive Summary

Showtime Sound & Lighting (SSL) Inc. needs a web-based business management system to replace their manual clipboard and Word document workflow. This MVP focuses on the core pain points: customer management, equipment tracking, and order/proposal generation.

## Problem Statement

SSL is experiencing:
- **Data duplication** across Word documents and spreadsheets
- **No equipment availability tracking** - risk of double-booking
- **Time-consuming document creation** for proposals, orders, invoices
- **Poor customer history access** affecting service quality
- **Manual data searching** for business decisions

Current scale: 50 active customers, $8,000 avg revenue/customer, 3 full-time employees

## MVP Scope

### Core Modules (Phase 1)

#### 1. Customer Management
- Create/edit/view customers
- Fields: ID, name, company, contact, phone, address, city, state, zip, fax
- View customer history (past orders/rentals)
- Search customers by name/company

#### 2. Equipment Inventory
- Create/edit/view equipment items
- Fields: ID, serial number, name, price (sale), rental rate, description, specifications
- Equipment categories: Audio, Video, Lighting
- Track equipment status: Available, Reserved, Out, Maintenance
- Maintenance due date tracking

#### 3. Orders/Proposals/Invoices
- Single document workflow (mark as Proposal → Order → Invoice)
- Link to customer
- Event details: date, location (event address, shipping address)
- Line items:
  - Equipment sales (with price)
  - Equipment rentals (with rental rate, dates)
  - Operator support (rate, hours)
- Auto-calculate totals
- Payment method, terms, tax exempt tracking
- Comments field

#### 4. Equipment Reservations
- Calendar view of equipment bookings
- Reserve equipment for date ranges
- Prevent double-booking
- Track: reservation date, event date, time out, time due, time returned, condition

