### User Interface (MVP Pages)

1. **Dashboard**
   - Today's events
   - Equipment out today
   - Recent orders
   - Quick actions

2. **Customers** (`/customers`)
   - List view with search
   - Create/edit customer modal
   - Customer detail page with order history

3. **Equipment** (`/equipment`)
   - List view with filters (category, status)
   - Create/edit equipment modal
   - Equipment detail page with rental history

4. **Orders** (`/orders`)
   - List view with filters (type, status)
   - Create/edit order page
   - Add line items (sales, rentals, operators)
   - Print/export proposal/invoice

5. **Calendar** (`/calendar`)
   - Monthly view of reservations
   - Equipment availability at-a-glance
   - Click to view/create reservation

### Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 (App Router), React, Tailwind CSS
- **Backend**: Next.js API Routes
- **Database**: MySQL (Railway)
- **Deployment**: Railway

### Phase 2 - Employee & Reporting (Current)

#### 5. Employee Management
- Create/edit/view employees (full-time and contract workers)
- Fields: ID, name, role (president/secretary/technician/contract), phone, address, skills, hourly rate, status
- Employee types:
  - Full-time: Tom (President), Martha (Secretary/Accounting), Burt & Ernie (Technicians)
  - Contract Workers: Equipment operators hired for events
- Performance notes for contract workers

#### 6. Employee Scheduling
- Assign employees to orders/events
- Track scheduled work: date, order/customer, required time in/out, actual time in/out, hours
- View employee schedules by date range
- Check availability before assignment
- Track overtime hours

#### 7. Basic Reporting
- **Equipment Utilization**: Which equipment is rented most, rental frequency, revenue per item
- **Customer Revenue**: Revenue by customer (sales, rentals, operator support)
- **Employee Hours**: Hours worked by employee, overtime tracking
- **Revenue Summary**: Monthly/yearly revenue by category (30% sales, 40% rental, 20% operator, 10% consulting)

